We first need to calculate the average total assets. The balance sheet shows that on 2023-12-31 the Total Assets were 16,000,000.00 and on 2024-02-04 the Total Assets were 19,520,226.07. Thus, the average total assets are computed as:

  Average Assets = (16,000,000.00 + 19,520,226.07) / 2
          = 35,520,226.07 / 2
          ≈ 17,760,113.04

The income statement gives a Net Profit of 143,922.03.

Now, the Return on Assets (ROA) is calculated as:

  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Assets) × 100%
    = (143,922.03 / 17,760,113.04) × 100%
    ≈ 0.81%

Thus, the ROA is approximately 0.81%.
